title: Instruments for ultra microspectrographic quantitative cytochemistry
display_string: Instruments for ultra microspectrographic quantitative cytochemistry, December 1954
repository_processing_note: Level 5 description created by Bethany Francis, 2011-08-1

subnotes.content:
From the Rockefeller Foundation's Photograph Accession Log, Binder #6, Accession Number 22849: "Title: Photos received with list of publications from the Inst. covering period of RF grant #49030." 

Torbjorn Caspersson sent Gerard Pomerat a December 9, 1953, report entitled, "Survey of the present state of the work on quantitative cytochemical procedures at the Institute for Cell Research, Medical Nobel Institute, Karolinska Institutet, Stockholm." Caspersson indicated in his covering letter of December 8, 1953, that he was also enclosing a list of reprints and seventeen figures.  In addition to photographs of the equipment, the figures include graphs and images of research results.
